  "body": "### Version Information\r\n\r\n* vyper Version (output of `vyper --version`): `0.3.6+commit.4a2124d`\r\n* OS: win\r\n* Python Version (output of `python --version`): `3.9.2`\r\n\r\n### What's your issue about?\r\n\r\nThe current Vyper version allows for calling `STATICCALL` via the `pure` modifier. But that opcode potentially allows to read from the environment or state and thus requires `view` IMHO.\r\n\r\nYou can reproduce this issue with my function [`multistaticcall`](https://github.com/pcaversaccio/snekmate/blob/main/src/utils/Multicall.vy#L180). IMHO this should be a `view` function but `pure` still compiles successfully...\r\n\r\n\r\n### How can it be fixed?\r\n\r\nFunctions that make use of the `STATICCALL` opcode must be declared as `view`.\r\n",
